fortinet.name: fortinet

revisions.description: Renamed to less ambiguous FORTIOS-300-MIB.
Spelling corrections. Added fnVpnDialupInOctets and fnVpnDialupOutOctets.
Added fnTrapPowerSupplyFailure (106) trap.
Added fnTrapTest (999) trap. Added new platforms: FG-30B, FG-5001A, FG-310B.
Improved descriptions.
Added spam counts to SMTP, POP3, and IMAP stats.
Corrected description of fnHaStatsNetUsage to Kbps. Added new per-vdom/per-protocol P2P statistics table.
Added fnIntfEntry as an augmentation of MIB-2 ifEntry. Added vdom indexes to admin and user tables. Removed unused OIDs. Updated ACCESS for some trap parameters.
Removed unused OID for per-vdom session count. Added missing model identifiers.
Refreshed for release, file formatting changes.
New statistics tables for applications such as proxies, VoIP and P2P. New stats for per vdom session counter and per policy byte counter.
New traps, model definitions, and extended vdom specific information for proxies and anti-virus. File formatting and cleanup. Intended for use with FortiOS 3.00 MR5 and newer.
Added new trap for internal use. Trap is to indicate completion of config deployment to the managing FortiManager.
Added new OIDs for non-dial-up VPN tunnels. Added new table and traps for hardware sensors.
Added new HA trap for heartbeat failure. Changed variables to use InetPortNumber as type, where appropriate. Added value range information to % fields. Added 1000A-LENC platform id.
Added new platforms to platform list.

Expanded traps to include sysName (hostname). Added new traps for other AV events, including oversize file blocking, file pattern matching, and fragmented file blocking. Renamed main AV trap to show actual usage.
Expanded vpn up/down traps and added OID's for local and remote gateway parameters. Updated Wifi platforms.
Added OID's for hdd usage and capacity. Added 5004 platform.
Added missing OID's for several traps used in communication between FortiGate and FortiManager. Also added some missing models. Moved fnIps group to correct OID.
Initial creation of unified MIB for products based on FortiOS >=3.00
